\"pagination\": {\n    \"has_more\": false,\n    \"limit\": 20,\n    \"next_offset\": null,\n    \"offset\": 0\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": 56235,\n      \"preview\": \"Bugfix: Amenities Map legend POI names were too long for the SVG legend column, so truncation now happens on whole-word boundaries with trailing separators removed. The helper `truncatePoiNameToWholeWord` uses a default display cap of 39 characters, which avoids clipped partial words in the right le\",\n      \"project\": \"/Users/lifcc/Desktop/code/work/mutil-om\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"source_type\": \"memory\",\n      \"staleness\": {\n        \"age\": \"fresh\",\n        \"label\": \"status=active; staleness=fresh; source_anchor=untracked\",\n        \"source_anchor\": \"untracked\",\n        \"status\": \"active\"\n      },\n      \"status\": \"active\",\n      \"title\": \"Amenities map legend POI names truncate on whole words\",\n      \"topic_key\": \"amenities-map-legend-poi-truncation\",\n      \"type\": \"bugfix\",\n      \"updated_at\": \"2026-06-16 13:24\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 79301,\n      \"preview\": \"On 2026-06-18, the remem GitHub queue was handled with threads/no-merge policy. Root worktree was dirty/stale, so isolated worktrees were used. Final remote state: PR #527 head 2317fbc, #529 head ca20e46, #531 head 2b2939a; all three open PRs had CI SUCCESS, mergeStateStatus CLEAN, and no unresolved\",\n      \"project\": \"remem\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"source_type\": \"memory\",\n      \"staleness\": {\n        \"age\": \"fresh\",\n        \"label\": \"status=active; staleness=fresh; source_anchor=untracked\",\n        \"source_anchor\": \"untracked\",\n        \"status\": \"active\"\n      },\n      \"status\": \"active\",\n      \"title\": \"June 18 GitHub queue cleanup for PRs 527, 529, 531\",\n      \"topic_key\": \"github-queue-2026-06-18-pr527-pr531\",\n      \"type\": \"bugfix\",\n      \"updated_at\": \"2026-06-18 14:18\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 79298,\n      \"preview\": \"Created draft PR #4 (https://github.com/air-codex/oopenit/pull/4) on branch codex/fix-mirror-security, commit efb0e65, to remediate mirror DB security and reliability issues introduced on main/DB_update. Root cause: mirror deployment and analytics code had hardcoded root/mirror credentials, default \",\n      \"project\": \"/Users/lifcc/Desktop/code/AI/tools/oopenit\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"source_type\": \"memory\",\n      \"staleness\": {\n        \"age\": \"fresh\",\n        \"label\": \"status=active; staleness=fresh; source_anchor=untracked\",\n        \"source_anchor\": \"untracked\",\n        \"status\": \"active\"\n      },\n      \"status\": \"active\",\n      \"title\": \"Mirror DB security and sync hardening PR\",\n      \"topic_key\": \"mirror-db-security-sync-hardening\",\n      \"type\": \"bugfix\",\n      \"updated_at\": \"2026-06-16 11:46\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 79295,\n      \"preview\": \"On 2026-06-14, processed the remem GitHub queue with the threads skill. PR #477 was independently reviewed via a native read-only reviewer lane, had head 60ec7abfaa85496f75dd6458a5fd08a53be48e72, CI check success, mergeState CLEAN, and GraphQL reviewThreads=0. It was squash-merged as ab8ad9e7e50711b\",\n      \"project\": \"/Users/lifcc/Desktop/code/AI/tools/remem\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"source_type\": \"memory\",\n      \"staleness\": {\n        \"age\": \"fresh\",\n        \"label\": \"status=active; staleness=fresh; source_anchor=untracked\",\n        \"source_anchor\": \"untracked\",\n        \"status\": \"active\"\n      },\n      \"status\": \"active\",\n      \"title\": \"PR #477 merged; #381 split into first M4 executable tranche\",\n      \"topic_key\": \"remem-pr477-m4-split-2026-06-14\",\n      \"type\": \"decision\",\n      \"updated_at\": \"2026-06-14 13:53\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 79303,\n      \"preview\": \"Merged bugfix for figure/grid translation layout breakage. Symptom: On docs.litellm.ai/blog/litellm-rust-launch, translated text in the Stage 1 diagram rendered vertically/heavily wrapped because whole-page/custom selectors accepted non-caption text inside a CSS-grid <figure>; inserted translation w\",\n      \"project\": \"/Users/lifcc/Desktop/code/AI/tools/page-lingo\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"source_type\": \"memory\",\n      \"staleness\": {\n        \"age\": \"fresh\",\n        \"label\": \"status=active; staleness=fresh; source_anchor=untracked\",\n        \"source_anchor\": \"untracked\",\n        \"status\": \"active\"\n      },\n      \"status\": \"active\",\n      \"title\": \"Skip non-caption figure internals to avoid grid diagram translation layout breakage\",\n      \"topic_key\": \"figure-visual-grid-translation-skip\",\n      \"type\": \"bugfix\",\n      \"updated_at\": \"2026-06-23 11:01\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 79297,\n      \"preview\": \"Resolved rclean open issue queue (#135 TOCTOU delete coverage/docs and #138 structured scan warnings) in branch codex/fix-open-issues-135-138. PR #155 was opened and squash-merged to main as bf62d9962f33e086caa647093f9c6399e9341f2e. Fixes: added ScanWarning and ScanReport.warnings, turned invalid CL\",\n      \"project\": \"rclean\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"source_type\": \"memory\",\n      \"staleness\": {\n        \"age\": \"fresh\",\n        \"label\": \"status=active; staleness=fresh; source_anchor=untracked\",\n        \"source_anchor\": \"untracked\",\n        \"status\": \"active\"\n      },\n      \"status\": \"active\",\n      \"title\": \"Resolved open issues #135 and #138 via PR #155\",\n      \"topic_key\": \"open-issues-135-138-merged-pr-155\",\n      \"type\": \"bugfix\",\n      \"updated_at\": \"2026-06-14 17:42\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 79299,\n      \"preview\": \"On 2026-06-17, after user requested non-GUI cleanup work via threads, created GitHub issues #156-#163 for remaining non-GUI rclean gaps. Implemented two PRs from origin/main bf62d996: PR #165 fixes #156 by making `clean --plan` honor ActionPlan `deleteMode`, rejecting conflicting CLI mode flags, and\",\n      \"project\": \"/Users/lifcc/Desktop/code/AI/tools/rclean\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"source_type\": \"memory\",\n      \"staleness\": {\n        \"age\": \"fresh\",\n        \"label\": \"status=active; staleness=fresh; source_anchor=untracked\",\n        \"source_anchor\": \"untracked\",\n        \"status\": \"active\"\n      },\n      \"status\": \"active\",\n      \"title\": \"Created non-GUI cleanup issues and PR fixes #164/#165\",\n      \"topic_key\": \"non-gui-cleanup-issues-prs-156-165\",\n      \"type\": \"bugfix\",\n      \"updated_at\": \"2026-06-16 16:51\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 79304,\n      \"preview\": \"PR #110 (`Tighten threads run logging and merge gates`) was merged on 2026-06-24T09:33:16Z with merge commit `05fee6aaf030396cc78d7fbd1f937785c6f0ec73`, closing issue #107 at 2026-06-24T09:33:17Z. The final head before merge was `f75a324e2bb03c823f53ca8c0b0722155abb462e`. Three Codex review threads \",\n      \"project\": \"/Users/lifcc/Desktop/code/AI/tools/claude-arsenal\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"source_type\": \"memory\",\n      \"staleness\": {\n        \"age\": \"fresh\",\n        \"label\": \"status=active; staleness=fresh; source_anchor=untracked\",\n        \"source_anchor\": \"untracked\",\n        \"status\": \"active\"\n      },\n      \"status\": \"active\",\n      \"title\": \"PR #110 merged after resolving connector merge-gate review threads\",\n      \"topic_key\": \"threads-pr110-delayed-review-recheck\",\n      \"type\": \"bugfix\",\n      \"updated_at\": \"2026-06-24 09:33\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 79296,\n      \"preview\": \"Open queue on 2026-06-15 had no PRs and issues #135/#138 only. Created clean worktree /tmp/rclean-all-issues from origin/main 5a8a87e and local branch codex/fix-open-issues-135-138, commit 1b12dfe `fix scan warnings and TOCTOU coverage`. #138 root cause: scan recoverable errors (.rcleanignore parse,\",\n      \"project\": \"/Users/lifcc/Desktop/code/AI/tools/rclean\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"source_type\": \"memory\",\n      \"staleness\": {\n        \"age\": \"fresh\",\n        \"label\": \"status=active; staleness=fresh; source_anchor=untracked\",\n        \"source_anchor\": \"untracked\",\n        \"status\": \"active\"\n      },\n      \"status\": \"active\",\n      \"title\": \"Fixed open issue tranche #135/#138 on local branch\",\n      \"topic_key\": \"open-issues-135-138-local-fix\",\n      \"type\": \"bugfix\",\n      \"updated_at\": \"2026-06-14 17:26\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 79300,\n      \"preview\": \"Chose the VibeGuard user-visible management page direction as a local-first `Project Operations` dashboard generated by the repo-local Codex App plugin, not a hosted telemetry/admin surface and not an unsupported custom Codex panel. The dashboard uses existing structured runtime data (`vibeguard-run\",\n      \"project\": \"/Users/lifcc/Desktop/code/AI/tools/vibeguard\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"source_type\": \"memory\",\n      \"staleness\": {\n        \"age\": \"fresh\",\n        \"label\": \"status=active; staleness=fresh; source_anchor=untracked\",\n        \"source_anchor\": \"untracked\",\n        \"status\": \"active\"\n      },\n      \"status\": \"active\",\n      \"title\": \"VibeGuard management UI is local-first Project Operations dashboard\",\n      \"topic_key\": \"project-operations-dashboard-design\",\n      \"type\": \"decision\",\n      \"updated_at\": \"2026-06-17 09:05\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 79305,\n      \"preview\": \"On 2026-06-24, completed the Spellbook open GitHub issue/PR queue using the threads workflow. Merged PR #110 (`Tighten threads run logging and merge gates`) with merge commit `05fee6aaf030396cc78d7fbd1f937785c6f0ec73`, closing issue #107. Merged PR #109 (`[codex] add scoped agent contracts`) with me\",\n      \"project\": \"/Users/lifcc/Desktop/code/AI/tools/claude-arsenal\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"source_type\": \"memory\",\n      \"staleness\": {\n        \"age\": \"fresh\",\n        \"label\": \"status=active; staleness=fresh; source_anchor=untracked\",\n        \"source_anchor\": \"untracked\",\n        \"status\": \"active\"\n      },\n      \"status\": \"active\",\n      \"title\": \"Closed remaining Spellbook issue/PR queue #109/#110/#112\",\n      \"topic_key\": \"spellbook-issue-pr-queue-20260624\",\n      \"type\": \"decision\",\n      \"updated_at\": \"2026-06-24 10:03\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 79306,\n      \"preview\": \"症状：QuotaBar 的 Local Cost 首次显示长期停在 “Loading cost...”。\\n\\n实测：在 2026-06-25 本机对 Claude 路径执行 `ccstats today/weekly/monthly --source claude --offline --json`，三次总 wall time 约 7.5s；每次日志 parse 仅 80-150ms，但 `Using cached pricing` 分别约 1.6-3.0s。ccstats SDK `summarize_cost` 每次都会重新 `PricingDb::load_quiet` 并解析 `~/.c\",\n      \"project\": \"/Users/lifcc/Desktop/code/AI/agent/quotabar\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"source_type\": \"memory\",\n      \"staleness\": {\n        \"age\": \"fresh\",\n        \"label\": \"status=active; staleness=fresh; source_anchor=untracked\",\n        \"source_anchor\": \"untracked\",\n        \"status\": \"active\"\n      },\n      \"status\": \"active\",\n      \"title\": \"QuotaBar Local Cost 慢加载根因与体验层缓存修复\",\n      \"topic_key\": \"local-cost-pricing-cache-slow-load\",\n      \"type\": \"bugfix\",\n      \"updated_at\": \"2026-06-24 16:34\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"structured_content":null},"error":null,"status":"completed"}}
